OL,3,CAnger as Bristol Rovers refers to
OL,4,C'disabled' and 'normal' fans
OL,6,FBristol Rovers has apologised after
OL,7,Fthe club referred to fans as
OL,8,F"disabled" and "normal" in an email.
OL,10,FThe club is introducing e-tickets for
OL,11,Fseason ticket holders and is offering
OL,12,Fa physical card to supporters who do
OL,13,Fnot want to have their ticket on their
OL,14,Fphone.
OL,16,FIn a private email exchange between
OL,17,Fthe club and a representative of its
OL,18,Fsupporters' club, Bristol Rovers said
OL,19,Fthat the #15 fee for those who want a
OL,20,Fphysical season card will be waived
OL,21,Ffor disabled fans.
